The paper deals with the problem of constructing a fast lossless code, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of subsets to group letters with small probabilities suggests a possible application in data structures (cs.DS) or distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the possibility of applying the scheme to sources with unknown statistics, which could be relevant to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.SI). Finally, the optimization of code length and speed could be of interest to researchers in the field of algorithms and complexity (cs.LG).
